class Solution {
    public int findChampion(int n, int[][] edges) {
        int[] degree = new int[n];
        for (int[] e : edges) {
            degree[e[1]]++;
        }
        int champion = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (degree[i] == 0) {
                if (champion == -1) {
                    champion = i;
                } else {
                    return -1;
                }
            }
        }
        return champion;
    }
}
```

The completed code first creates an array 'degree' to count the in-degree of each node. It then iterates through the given edges, incrementing the in-degree of the 'to' node for each edge. After that, it goes through each node, checking if its in-degree is 0. If there is more than one node with 0 in-degree, then there is no unique champion and it returns -1. Otherwise, it returns the node number of the unique champion.

